reviewText: Extremely long videos and a huge variety of frameworks made this course hard to manage through. Without a central narrative or a central 'challenge' that we were applying the framework to, I felt that it was just theory on top of theory throughout the whole course. I love a good framework, however, when the frameworks rely on language that seems like it could be switched between any of them, it makes it hard to a) remember which theory goes where, and b) makes it hard to bring out into real life.
